  "text": "Immunohistochemistry against 3F4 detecting phosphorylated CRMP2 (pCRMP2) at pT509/pS518/pS522 showed pCRMP2 + neurons as early as Braak I in the EC, subiculum and hippocampal CA1-3 fields and we found that the number of pCRMP2 + neurons were correlated with Braak stages (Fig. 1C and Table 1 ). In addition, we observed co-localization of pCRMP2 and pS422 pTau in the CA1 field as determined by immunostaining of the adjacent sections of human brain tissue with 3F4 (for pCRMP2) and PS422 (for pTau, Figure 1D ). Pervious study reported that colocalization of TTBK1 with PS422 in pre-tangle neurons determined by immunohistochemistry with AD and non-symptomatic control brain samples [CITATION_1] , indicating a synergistic effect with TTBK1 and pCRMP2 in early tau pathology.",
